From: NuttX RP2350 maintainers <noreply@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] netutils/netlib: use the configured listen backlog

netlib_listenon() hard-codes a backlog of five even when NuttX is configured
to support more pending TCP connections.  This causes avoidable connection
resets during short HTTP bursts.  Use SOMAXCONN so the listener follows
CONFIG_NET_TCPBACKLOG_CONNS and the platform default.

---
 netutils/netlib/netlib_listenon.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/netutils/netlib/netlib_listenon.c b/netutils/netlib/netlib_listenon.c
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/netutils/netlib/netlib_listenon.c
+++ b/netutils/netlib/netlib_listenon.c
@@ -114,7 +114,7 @@ int netlib_listenon(uint16_t portno)
 
   /* Listen for connections on the bound TCP socket */
 
-  if (listen(listensd, 5) < 0)
+  if (listen(listensd, SOMAXCONN) < 0)
     {
       nerr("ERROR: listen failure %d\n", errno);
       netlib_server_activity_hook("listen-fail", portno);
